    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-09T05:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-09T05:00:00-05:00" n="817"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d817">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.0443/12–944: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-09T17:00:00+07:00"
                            >December 9, 1944—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 9—10:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1988. Foreign Office states that as commercial law is embodied in existing
                    Chinese civil code, there is not intention to draft separate commercial law at
                    present (ReDeptel 1430, November 3, 10 p.m.).</p>
                <p>Chinese laws [<hi rend="italic">News</hi>] Service article may refer to statement
                    of general principles governing postwar economic development (ReEmbs 1864,
                    November 19, 9 a.m.; 1974, December 8 and 1975, December 8, 8 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >9</hi>] a.m.<note n="65" xml:id="d817fn65">Concerning telegram No. 1975,
                        see footnote 64, <ref target="#pg_1092">p. 1092</ref>.</note>) and possibly
                    also to statement on commercial policies (ReEmbs 1865, November 19, 10 a.m., and
                    1978, December 8, 11 a.m. and ReDeptel 1522, November 23, 5 p.m.)</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
